Defines the typed error hierarchy for the steno compiler pipeline — one error type per pipeline stage, all implementing `std::error::Error` and `Display`. Nothing in the crate panics or swallows failures; every fallible operation returns one of these.

Five error types, each a thin wrapper around a `message: String`: `StrokeError` (parsing/rendering/merging strokes and count-bank arithmetic), `StenoError` (top-level parse errors, uniquely carrying a 1-based `line: usize` via `line()`), `ExpandError` (count/type expansion pass), `RenderError` (rendering pass — unresolved chunk reaching a renderer, or a movement not up-and-left of the resting cursor), and `SnippetError` (snippet renderer — unresolved chunk reaching it). All constructors (`new`) are `pub(crate)`, so external callers can only construct these via the crate's public API, not directly.

The one non-obvious piece of logic: `impl From<StrokeError> for ExpandError` converts by restringifying via `to_string()`, deliberately discarding the original error's structure to preserve the message text only — noted in a comment as matching the original TS pipeline's behavior of letting stroke errors propagate unwrapped into expansion context. All types derive `Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq`, so they're comparable in tests and cloneable across pipeline stages. `StenoError::line()` is the only accessor beyond `Display`; other error types expose no structured data beyond their rendered message, so callers needing more than the string must match on error variant/type, not inspect fields.